Reynagh. This convent was founded about the middle of‘ the sixth century by St. Reynagh, otherwise Regnacia, sister to St. Finnian of Glonard. She was abbess here and died in 563. Her mother Talacia succeeded her as abbess. The site of the old church of Reynagh and its ruins may be seen in the present town of Banagher, where it is situated. She is patroness of the parish which is called by her name. The present Convent at Banagher is called St. Reynagh'S‚ and is conducted by the Sisters of Ste Union des Sacros Coeurs. The old church of Saran lies in ruins about the centre of Moystown demesne, to the west of the river Brosna. The holy well of St. Saran is south-west of Moystown House. Saran was sent from Olonmacnoise to found his church near the Brosna.
